radiographic_examinations.findings: The proximal portion of the visualized appendix appears normal as it fills with contrast and air; however, the more distal portion of the appendix is dilated up to 8 mm and does not fill with contrast or air. There is minimal fat stranding in this region. The visualized lung bases are clear, normal appearing heart, spleen, adrenals, pancreas, gallbladder, liver, normal kidneys enhancing and excreting contrast, widely patent abdominal aorta and branches, no free air or free fluid, no significant adenopathy, normal stomach and abdominal loops of small bowel.
